# Vitis AI 3.5

This directory contains the Vitis AI 3.5 patch for our YOLOv8 deployment, which includes modifications and optimizations for inference on the xView3-SAR dataset.

## Installation
Download the Vitis AI 3.5 framework (3.5 release) from the [Vitis AI GitHub](https://github.com/Xilinx/Vitis-AI). Apply the patch in this directory to the Vitis AI framework source code.
```bash
cd vitis_ai
git apply ../framework/vitis_ai/xview3_yolov8_v3.5.patch
```
Follow the build instructions in the Vitis AI documentation to cross-compile the framework with the applied patch with Petalinux. The compiled binaries can be transferred to the Kria KV260 MPSoC in `/usr/local/` for deployment.

## Framework Modifications

1. **Image Loading:** To read TIFF files, the `cv::IMREAD_UNCHANGED` flag must be added to every `cv::imread` call. in `ReadImagesThread`.
2. **Custom Image Normalization:** Linear normalization of SAR bands and bathymetry is modified in `image_preprocess`: 
    ```c++
    cv::subtract(image_tmp, cv::Scalar(-6000.0, -50.0, -50.0), image_tmp);
    cv::divide(image_tmp, cv::Scalar(8000.0, 70.0, 70.0), image_tmp);
    cv::min(image_tmp, 1.0, image_tmp);
    cv::max(image_tmp, 0.0, image_tmp);
    top = round(dh - 0.1);
    int bottom = round(dh + 0.1);
    left = round(dw - 0.1);
    int right = round(dw + 0.1);
    // Convert to BGR
    cv::cvtColor(image_tmp, image_tmp, cv::COLOR_RGB2BGR);
    // Convert to *signed* 8-bit
    image_tmp.convertTo(output_image, CV_8S, 255, -128);
    ```
3. **Modified IoU Metrics:** Added PIoU2 calculation in `applyNMS`.
4. **Post-Processing** Optimized `yolov8_post_process` method to handle the added predictions of the P2 architecture, accelerating decoding of the prediction by a factor of 27.

